args: It's time for all good little boys and girls\nto be in bed! Ninja art...Shadow Stitch!
Looks like Aoi is on night watch tonight.\nHer techniques may prove troublesome...
One sends a shinobi to fight a shinobi.\nLeave this to me.
But then what will become of you?
There is no greater honor than to fight for\none's brethren. Now go while I do this.\nNinja art...Shadow Stitch Reversal!
The tale begins earlier that morning...
Okay, my turn! I rolled 12 in total, so I'm\ngonna attack with my shock trooper!
Sorry, pal, but I got a shield knight and a\nheavy cavalry lying in ambush there.
Eugene's counteroffensive wipes out\nHope's forces entirely. That's game.
This tale of tabletop war ends here.\nSkillfully done, Eugene.
Sounds like you guys're havin' fun.\n*yaaawn*
And you sound wiped. Hanging out until\nthe wee hours again, Ranzal?
Yeah, wild night on the town—for purely\nwork reasons, I'll have ya know.
Mercs and adventurers gotta cut loose to\nstay limber, which means the city's full'a\nthem types once the sun beats feet.
And since those guys and gals got the intel\nwe need to fight this war, my wild ways're\npurely for networkin' and reconnaissance.
Getting in good with the nightlife and\ngathering intelligence?\nYou've piqued my interest!
Yeah! Sounds like just the sort of thing a\nwarrior should be doing!
Take us with you next time, Ranzal!
Sorry, champ. No can do. Yer a little young\nto be runnin' amok with the likes'a Ranzal.
He just treated us like a bunch of kids!\nThat was low...
But as we also fight under the Halidom's\nbanner, I believe his demeanor unfounded.
Right? We're TOTALLY warriors!\nSo I vote that tonight we... *whisper*
I can't believe Operation: Sneak Out Of\nThe Castle Alone And Party With Ranzal\njust started and Jurota's ALREADY down.
No way! We can't waste his sacrifice.\nWe've gotta push through the tears\nand keep moving forward!
That's right! We're gonna avenge Jurota\nand the meat by going... Wait, meat?
Gah! We're under attaaaack!\nWait, is she sleepwalking?
Mayday! Mayday! She's gonna eat meeee!
There's gotta be a way to calm her down!
It's a gamble, but... You two, stand back!\nArcane barrier, unfold!
You stopped her in her tracks...\nWhere'd you pick up THAT trick?
A magic studies textbook, though this is\nmy first time putting it to actual use.\nI'm pleased it worked out.
Nice one, Nicolas. Okay, let's get going!

Would that I could. But I'm afraid I have
to remain here to maintain the spell until
she calms down. Alas, fellows, my path
ends here.
No! We can't lose you, too!
Please don't look so sad. Using knowledge\nI found in one of my books to actually help\nmy friends is a complete win for me.
No more looking back. Go and enjoy the\nnight's pleasures in my stead!
We finally made it outside! Now we just\nhave to get past the gates and we're—
Mmm, the breeze feels so nice...\nIt's the perfect night for extra training.
(Look! It's Celliera! If she spots us,\nshe'll ruin the plan AND make us do\npush-ups until we hurl!)
(One time, I saw her catch the prince\ntrying to sneak out and she put him\nthrough a ＂lifestyle correction＂ course!)
Right! There's 500 midnight wind sprints.\nNow for my ten thousand nightly squats.\n...One! ...Two! ...Three! ...Four!
(Uh, do we have to wait until she's done?\n'Cause ten thousand is a LOT.)
(Knowing her, she'll move on to something\nelse as soon as she finishes squatting...)
(No other choice: I'll act as bait and draw\nher off while you make for the gate!)
(Don't worry! Tobias trained me well;\nmy legs can handle it.)
(This plan is stupid. If you're gonna be bait,\nthen I'M gonna be bait!)
(We split and run for the gate from different\ndirections, yeah? If she gets one of us,\nthe other one keeps going.)
(And you don't get a veto. If there's risk,\nwe're gonna share it equally.)
(One for all and all for one, eh?\nCopy that, partner!)
They're moving separately.\nI'll start with the closer one!
*gasp* *wheeze* Made it...to the gates...\nBut where's Eugene?
Is that all you've got, soldier?!\nSwing those arms! Lift those knees!
Ma'am, yes, ma'am!\nONE, two, three, four!\nTWO, two, three, four!
I won't let your sacrifices be in vain,\neveryone... I promise.
I'll carry your memories with me as I head\nout to an unforgettable night on the tow—
Ranzal?! What are you doing here?!
Figured ya squirts would try somethin' like\nthis, so I decided to lay a trap for ya.
City's a dangerous place at night for the\nsame reasons what make it fun, so ya\ngotta keep yer head on a swivel.
And if yer gettin' busted by the likes'a me,\nya ain't ready for the city. Now c'mon, kid.\nLet's get ya back to bed.
She kept me training until dawn,\nand I'm literally dying. *yaaawn*
Yes, and I had to keep that barrier up\nall night as well. *yaaawn*
Aoi and I were evenly matched, and our\nbattle stretched on to daybreak. *yaaawn*
I'm so sorry, you guys! You all put your\nbodies on the line, and I couldn't...
You faced an opponent beyond your skill,\nnothing more. There is no apology needed.
He's right. And so is Ranzal, frankly—\nwe'd have made a pack of easy marks for\nstreet toughs or shady merchants.
Plus it was fun, even if we lost;\nsneaking out at night is peak youth!
Hats off to the solidarity, boys!\nStill, I can't have ya sneakin' off again.

So I'll make ya a promise: You four get
a little more experience under yer belts,
and this old man'll take ya out on the
town personally.
You bet. It's a promise between warriors!
